def demonstrate_file(file):
    if isinstance(file, str):
        data = joblib.load(file)
    else:
        data = file
    n_images = 4
       
    images = [data.raw_image, data.traced_image, data.traced_binary_mask]
    titles = ['Raw Image', 'Traced Image', 'Masked Traced Image']
    if 'traced_multilabel_mask' in data.get_attributes():
        images.append(data.traced_multilabel_mask)
        titles.append('Labeled Traced Image')
    images.append(data.predicted)
    titles.append('Predicted Image')
    if 'predicted_postprocessed' in data_.get_attributes():
        images.append(data.predicted_postprocessed)
        titles.append('Post-processed Predictions')
        
    n_cols = 2
    n_rows = math.ceil(len(images) / n_cols)
    
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(n_rows, n_cols, figsize=(8*1.5, 10*1.5))
    fig.tight_layout(pad=0, h_pad=0.5, w_pad=0 )
    axes = axes.reshape(-1)
    
    for image, title, ax in zip(images, titles, axes):
        ax.imshow(image)
        ax.set_title(title)
        
    for ax in axes:
        ax.axis('off')
        
    for i in range(len(images), len(axes)):
        axes[i].axis('off')
        
def demonstrate_file(file, attrs=None, drop_attrs=[], n_cols=2):
    if isinstance(file, str):
        data = joblib.load(file)
    else:
        data = file
    n_images = 4
       
    if attrs is None:
        attrs = ['raw_image', 'traced_image', 'traced_binary_mask', 
                 'traced_multilabel_mask', 'predicted', 'predicted_postprocessed']
    titles = {
        'raw_image': 'Raw Image', 
        'traced_image': 'Traced Image', 
        'traced_binary_mask': 'Masked Traced Image', 
        'traced_multilabel_mask': 'Labeled Traced Image', 
        'predicted': 'Raw Predictions', 
        'predicted_postprocessed': 'Post-processed Predictions'
    }
    
    images_and_titles = [(getattr(data, attr), titles[attr]) 
                         for attr, title in zip(attrs, titles)
                         if attr in data.get_attributes()
                         and attr not in drop_attrs
                        ]
        
    n_rows = math.ceil(len(images_and_titles) / n_cols)
    
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(n_rows, n_cols, figsize=(12 * n_cols // 2, 15))
    fig.tight_layout(pad=0, h_pad=0.5, w_pad=0 )
    axes = axes.reshape(-1)
    
    for (image, title), ax in zip(images_and_titles, axes):
        ax.imshow(image)
        ax.set_title(title)
        
    for ax in axes:
        ax.axis('off')
        
    for i in range(len(images_and_titles), len(axes)):
        axes[i].axis('off')

from itertools import zip_longest
def show_traced_lever_arms(files, titles=[]):
    fig, axes = plt.subplots(len(files), 2, figsize=(8*1.5, 10*1.5))
    axes = axes.reshape(-1, 2)
    fig.tight_layout(pad=0, h_pad=0.5, w_pad=0 )
    for i, (file, title) in enumerate(zip_longest(files, titles, fillvalue='')):
        data = joblib.load(file)
        data.get_traced_contours(90)
        axes[i, 0].imshow(data.raw_image)
        axes[i, 0].set_title('Raw Image')
        axes[i, 1].imshow(data.traced_lever_arm_images[90])
        axes[i, 1].set_title(r'90$^o$ Lever Arms')
    for ax in axes.reshape(-1):
        ax.axis('off')

show_traced_lever_arms(files_, titles=[''])

def fill_zero_with_random_class(img):
    zero_indcs = np.where(img == 0)
    classes = sorted(np.unique(img))
    p = np.ones_like(classes)
    p[0] = 30
    p = p / p.sum()
    out = img.copy()
    random_values = np.random.choice(classes, len(zero_indcs[0]), p=p)
    out[zero_indcs] = random_values
    return out
